# Next.js Site Stack (MgonnacrushT)

This repo is a **Next.js 15 static export** site (Jekyll removed). Domain: `mgonnacrusht.co.uk`.

## Stack and config

- `output: 'export'`, `trailingSlash: true`, `images.unoptimized: true` in `next.config.ts`
- Light-only v1; Tailwind v4 + Framer Motion (`FadeIn` respects `prefers-reduced-motion`)
- Central config: `lib/config/site.ts` (`showRoadmap`, `playStoreUrl`, Formspree ID, Umami, emails)
- User-facing copy lives in `lib/content/` (i18n-ready; English only for now via `lib/i18n/`)

## Page map

- `/` agency-first; `/services/`; `/products/` (Portfolio label, URL unchanged); `/savet/` flagship case study; `/about/`; `/contact/`
- Legal (verbatim text, do not change URLs): `/legal/privacy/`, `/legal/terms/`, `/savet/legal/privacy/`, `/savet/legal/terms/`
- `/savet/roadmap/` hidden by default (`showRoadmap: false`, noindex, not in sitemap)

## Integrations

- **Contact:** `@formspree/react` in `components/contact/ContactForm.tsx` (form ID `mwvdyvkr`, honeypot `_gotcha`). No raw HTML form POST.
- **Play Store CTA:** hidden until `NEXT_PUBLIC_PLAY_STORE_URL` is set. No early-access CTA on public site.
- **Analytics:** Umami script in `app/layout.tsx`
- **SEO:** `lib/seo/metadata.ts`, `app/sitemap.ts`, `app/robots.ts`, `components/seo/JsonLd.tsx`

## Build and deploy

```bash
npm run build   # legacy redirects → next build → copy CNAME to out/
```

- Deploy: GitHub Actions on push to `main` (`.github/workflows/deploy.yml`); Pages source = GitHub Actions
- `CNAME` lives in `public/CNAME` only
- Legacy `/features/*` → `/savet/`: Cloudflare 301 (primary) — see `docs/cloudflare-config.md`; fallback: `scripts/generate-legacy-redirects.mjs`

## UI components

Prefer 21st.dev blocks via full URL (no fake `--registry` flag):

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add "https://21st.dev/r/<author>/<component>"
```

If no suitable block, compose minimal Tailwind/shadcn primitives — avoid large bespoke UI.

## Content sync

When SaveT or site messaging changes, update `assets/savet_prompt_agent_summary.txt` with `Last updated: YYYY-MM-DD`.
